ffer the human intellect the means whereby civilization may be carried triumphantly forward.\n\n- Winston\n|\nIf you emulate the behaviours of confident people, you will help yourself to become confident.\n\n- Sam Owen, 500 Relationships And Life Quotes: Bite-Sized Advice For Busy People\n|\nNever let the future disturb you. You will meet it, if you have to, with the same weapons of reason which today arm you against the present.\n\n- Marcus Aurelius, Meditations\n|\nOur knowledge is limited. However, reading augments our knowledge.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nYes she met with a slight accident involving a stake.' Ash said 'funny how that happens sometimes...\n\n- L.J. Smith, Night World, No. 1\n|\nAll the world is queer save thee and me, and even thou art a little queer.\n\n- Robert\n|\nWhen you perceive a truth, look for the balancing truth.\n\n- John\n|\nKatey's the hottest bookworm you'll ever meet. If you took all the books that she's read and piled them in a stack, you could climb to the Milky Way.\n\n- Amor Towles, Rules of Civility\n|\nModern tragic writers have to write short stories; if they wrote long stories…cheerfulness would creep in. Such stories are like stings; brief, but purely painful.\n\n- G.K. Chesterton, Alarms and Discursions\n|\n...Thought lengths it, pulls an invisible world through a needle's eye one detail at a time, ...\n\n- Jennifer Grotz, The Needle\n|\nWe all have pain, Wes. It isn't life without it. What matters in life isn't that we escape pain. What matters is that we overcome it.\n\n- Heidi Cullinan, A Private Gentleman\n|\nAnd must I then, indeed, Pain, live with youall through my life?-sharing my fire, my bed,Sharing-oh, worst of all things!-the same head?-And, when I feed myself, feeding you too?\n\n- Edna St. Vincent Millay, Mine the Harvest\n|\nMindset matters... always. The difference found between the victorious and the envious, the successful and the haters; is mindset.\n\n- Steve\n|\nThere is much you can learn from books and scrolls. These books are my friends, my companions. They make me laugh and cry and find meaning in life.\n\n- Christopher Paolini, Eragon\n|\nTruthfully, wicked people reveal themselves in words first, to inhibit speech would inhibit us seeing the wicked before they act.\n\n- Leviak B. Kelly, Religion: The Ultimate STD: Living a Spiritual Life without Dogmatics or Cultural Destruction\n|\nMaybe he was old-fashioned, but to him a couple meant a strong bond, with positive and negative charges constantly arcing between them.\n\n- Stewart O'Nan, Songs for the Missing\n|\nA man’s true world should be the space and people that enrich his soul,\n\n- Janvier Chouteu-Chando, Disciples of Fortune\n|\nInvestigation?' Isabelle laughed. 'Now we're detectives? Maybe we should all have code names.''Good idea,' said Jace. 'I shall be Baron Hotschaft Von Hugenstein.\n\n- Cassandra Clare, City of Bones\n|\nKeep walking on the path of bravery. Keep walking on the path of your passion. Keep walking, and do not stop until you reach your goal.\n\n- Abhijit\n|\nI mean, if the relationship can't survive the long term, why on earth would it be worth my time and energy for the short term?\n\n- Nicholas Sparks, The Last Song\n|\nNo matter how dysfunctional your background, how broke or broken you are, where you are today, or what anyone else says, YOU MATTER, and your life matters!\n\n- Germany\n|\nMoney is numbers and numbers never end. If it takes money to be happy, your search for happiness will never end.\n\n- Bob\n|\nParanoia is transmissible from mind to mind, but it does not go by the route of reason. It can therefore change its rationalization while remaining essentially the same.\n\n- William Nicholls, Christian Antisemitism\n|\nThis is where I belong, burning in these flames. For everything I have done wrong, I know I am to blame.\n\n- Atarah L. Poling, Hidden Light\n|\nResolve, and thou art free.\n\n- Henry Wadsworth Longfellow, Flower-de-Luce, and the Masque of Pandora\n|\nIn real life, second chances are rare. I therefore advise you to take every single chance very seriously.\n\n- Abdurrahman\n|\nFreedom's just another word for 'nothing left to lose'.\n\n- Kris\n|\nYou had this expression on your face, like you weren’t quite sure you were supposed to be on Earth.\n\n- pleasefindthis, I Wrote This For You\n|\nAge is only a number. Maturity to a large extent is dependent on your exposure to life, its experiences and your lessons from them.\n\n- Omoakhuana\n|\nWe are never allowed to forget that some books are badly written; we should remember that sometimes they're badly read, too.\n\n- Nick Hornby, The Polysyllabic Spree\n|\nFor young adults,the growth from silly to serious can be very fast, indeed.\n\n- Dean\n|\nOnce you leave out all the bullshit they teach you in school, life gets really simple.\n\n- George Carlin, Brain Droppings\n|\nIt is impossible to discourage the real writers - they don't give a damn what you say, they're going to write.\n\n- Sinclair\n|\nI hear you speak in songs of love, written for me only. And though I wander far too much, the path is rarely lonely.\n\n- Atalina Wright, Unbound\n|\nFear, left unchecked, can spread like a virus.\n\n- Lish McBride, Necromancing the Stone\n|\nWe were all born equal, but where we are in life now is of our own making.\n\n- Stephen\n|\nOur hearts, the war.Her body, the battlefield.\n\n- Rick Yancey, The Last Star\n|\nWhy did adults have to be so thick? They always say “tell the truth,” and when you do, they don’t believe you. What’s the point?\n\n- Rick Riordan, The Red Pyramid\n|\nKnow that there is often hidden in us a dormant poet, always young and alive.\n\n- Paul\n|\nI go back for seconds and thirds and fourths and fifths, when it’s good. Just not if it means some guy gets to put a leash on me.\n\n- Paula Stokes, The Key to Everything\n|\nEverything changes in my life, and the world stays the same.\n\n- Cassandra Clare, City of Ashes\n|\nTo enjoy the magnificence of life, drink every drop of life and get drunk.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nContemporary poets got so obscure that poetry kind of fell out of favor,\n\n- Paul\n|\nIf one knew the truth how could there be freedom? If hell and paradise were in the middle of the marketplace, everyone would be a saint.\n\n- Isaac Bashevis Singer, The Collected Stories of Isaac Bashevis Singer\n|\nThey do not realize that a myth is dead if it no longer lives and grows. Our myth has become mute, and gives no answers.\n\n- C.\n|\nEven though God has given the gift of time to all men equally, it is what each man does with this equal gift of time that determines whether or not he will be great.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, How To Become Great Through Time Conversion: Are you wasting time, spending time or investing time?\n|\nIt doesn’t matter your area of calling, you can invest quality time into it, you will definitely become the best and that will buy you greatness.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, The Veritable Source of Energy\n|\nConsciousness cannot be glimpsed as though it were something outside yourself, because it is you.\n\n- Belsebuub, Self-Knowledge for Spiritual Awakening\n|\nFaith has power in it. More often than not, faith can create miracles.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nIf the spirit of your imagination is limited, your journey of discovery will be very short.\n\n- Alastair Agutter, The Theory of Particle Matter Frequencies and Multiple Universes\n|\nOnly Irish coffee provides in a single glass all four essential food groups: alcohol, caffeine, sugar and fat.\n\n- Alex\n|\nThe truth was, history repeated itself on a daily basis; mistakes were made over and over. People were haunted by what they had done, and by what they hadn't had time to do.\n\n- Jodi\n|\nI always thought the joy of reading a book is not knowing what happens next. (Leonard Shelby, Memento)\n\n- Christopher\n|\nWhen you finally learn that you are not the smartest person in the room- you will build a better product, have better relationships, and eliminate wasted time.\n\n- Colleen\n|\nLife does not accommodate you; it shatters you. Every seed destroys its container, or else there would be no fruition.\n\n- Florida Scott-Maxwell, The Measure of My Days\n|\nAchievement is no hocus-pocus. It's focus, focus!\n\n- Ana Claudia Antunes, A-Z of Happiness: Tips for Living and Breaking Through the Chain that Separates You from Getting That Dream Job\n|\nWhat You were Once, Was Also Because You Were Someone Else Before that\n\n- Sujit Lalwani, Life Simplified!\n|\nWhen we let our GREED become our NEED, we can never be HAPPY indeed!-RVM\n\n- RVM\n|\nYou don’t need money to be kind, but you cannot be kind without a heart.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nAll any of us wanted, really, was to know that we counted. That someone else's life would not have been as rich without us here.\n\n- Jodi Picoult, Handle with Care\n|\nmy only complaints are two:that I didn't make myself readyfor you sooner in life, thatI can't give you better,Love you more.\n\n- Jan\n|\nYou move forward. You face up to your challenges. You don't retreat. You're young, and sometimes you'll wish you could. But don't.\n\n- Ellyn Bache, The Art of Saying Goodbye\n|\nA man must be prepared to face life, as well as death, there's no escape from either.\n\n- Ellis Peters, Dead Man's Ransom\n|\nThe true life is not reducible to words spoken or written, not by anyone, ever.\n\n- Don DeLillo, Point Omega\n|\nBernie believed in God. He believed that God wanted people to enjoy life to the fullest, not drench themselves in aversion and prejudice.\n\n- Rebecca McNutt, Bittersweet Symphony\n|\nDying is an art.Like everything else,I do it exceptionally well.I do it so it feels like hell.I do it so it feels real.I guess you could say I have a call.\n\n- Sylvia Plath, Ariel\n|\nand every day I thank [God] that I am alive, not because I fear death, but because my wife has a husband and my son is not an orphan.\n\n- Khaled\n|\nIf I had a camera,' I said, 'I'd take a picture of you every day. That way I'd remember how you looked every single day of your life.\n\n- Nicole\n|\nIf one cannot enjoy reading a book over and over again, there is no use in reading it at all.\n\n- Oscar\n|\nIf you believe you can, you might. If you know you can, you will.\n\n- Steve Maraboli, Life, the Truth, and Being Free\n|\nMy life has been one great big joke,A dance that's walked,A song that's spoke,I laugh so hard I almost choke,When I think about myself.\n\n- Maya\n|\nBut,instead of what our imagination makes us suppose and which we worthless try to discover,life gives us something that we could hardly imagine.\n\n- Marcel\n|\nMother Dear, one day I'm going to turn this world upside down.'--From My Brother Martin, by Christine King Farris\n\n- Martin\n|\nIn the pursuit of knowledge, no one should travel alone\n\n- C.S. Woolley, Rising Empire: Part 2\n|\nWhat we most love is not what we know, but what knows us and draws us. . . . (78)\n\n- Ravi Ravindra, The Wisdom of Patanjali's Yoga Sutras: A New Translation and Guide by Ravi Ravindra\n|\nProgress in science depends on new techniques, new discoveries and new ideas, probably in that order.\n\n- Sidney\n|\nOh yes! I have couple-goals too. I love to couple myself with- Books, Coffee and Mountains.\n\n- Jasleen\n|\nBreathtaking, splendid, wondrous, sublime, all those words describe you, exactly as you are. You are a work of art! Enjoy your beauty!\n\n- Amy\n|\nLove does not leave, it grows and transforms into something different.\n\n- Staci\n|\nListen to me. They may control what you do, but no one can pee on your soul without your permission.\n\n- A.S. King, Everybody Sees the Ants\n|\nHaving one king, one god, one belief, they can act single-mindedly.\n\n- Ursula K. Le Guin, Voices\n|\nPhilosophy, as we use the word, is a fight against the fascination which forms of expression exert upon us.\n\n- Ludwig Wittgenstein, کتاب آبی\n|\nWhen you have discovered your significance, your life will now begin to move towards making a difference.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, The Mountain of Ignorance\n|\nMany people walk in and out of your life, but only true friends will leave footprints in your heart.\n\n- Windhy Puspitadewi, Confeito\n|\nFor you not to waste or spend your life, you must first begin to see time and life correctly.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, How To Become Great Through Time Conversion: Are you wasting time, spending time or investing time?"